data.title: Popular Comedian David Spade Has Sold Out Michigan Stand
data.meta_description: Famous for quick wit on SNL, sitcoms and many movies... This show is certain to entertain.
data.text:
Michigan fans of comedy should be excited for "one of our own" to take the stage with a new stand-up show at Royal Oak Music Theater.

We have all the info you need to get the laughs.

See Also: Will Michigan Get a New Spin-off Restaurant from Mickey D's?

David Spade performing in Metro Detroit

Comedian and actor, David Spade was born in Birmingham, Michigan. So, this performance is like a homecoming.

Fans will get to see Spade perform on a tour that will take him all over the United States in 2024.

David Spade Stand Up Comedy Show in Michigan Information

Metro Detroit's Royal Oak Music Theater is hosting David Spade on January 13th at 7pm.

Hopefully you already have tickets, because the show sold-out in a hurry.

Tickets were available for purchase through axs or at Royal Oak Music Theater. Prices range from $45.00-$75.00. No word if another show will be added, at this time.

This is the second of only two shows scheduled for January. The other is in Chicago the night before.

David Spade Movies and TV Shows

Fans have probably seen most of these comedies.

Grown Ups 1 and 2

The Wrong Missy

Joe Dirt (cool merch on his website for this, btw)

Tommy Boy

Reality Bites

Those are just a few of the movies. He has also provided voices for animated films, too.

Spade's TV shows were funny, too.

Just Shoot Me

Rules of Engagement

8 Simple Rules (after John Ritter died)

and more

His latest TV gig is hosting a game show, Snake Oil, on FOX.
